p:
Several plants of this taxon are covered with glandular trichomes that produce and store essential oils. Due to the odor conferred by these oils, the plants are very popular in rural areas of Latin America, where they are used as pest repellents and for treating respiratory and gastrointestinal disorders, among others (
 Agra et al., 2007; 
 Pinheiro et al., 2015; 
 Arruda et al., 2016). Activities such as antinociceptive, antimicrobial and insecticidal have been reported, endorsing the traditional use of some species (
 Nascimento et al., 2008; 
 McNeil et al., 2011).
